President Trump held a press briefing to announce new guidelines for Americans to follow over the next 15 days in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The guidelines include recommendations for young and healthy people to engage in schooling from home, avoid gatherings of more than 10 people, avoid discretionary travel, and avoid eating and drinking at bars, restaurants, and public food courts. The President also mentioned that a vaccine candidate has begun a clinical trial and that efforts are being made to develop antiviral therapies and other treatments. He emphasized the importance of everyone working together to stop the spread of the virus. The President and his team also addressed questions about testing, healthcare resources, the economy, and other related topics.